President Joseph R. Biden, Jr. has announced the designation of a Presidential Delegation to attend the Inauguration of Rodrigo Alberto de Jesús Chaves Robles as President of Costa Rica on May 8, 2022. The delegation will be led by Miguel Cardona, the United States Secretary of Education. Other members of the delegation include Cynthia Telles, the United States Ambassador to Costa Rica, Uzra Zeya, the Under Secretary for Civilian Security, Democracy, and Human Rights at the U.S. Department of State, and Cristóbal Alex, the Special Assistant to the President and White House Deputy Cabinet Secretary.